      <ol>
	<li>HTML - Main document type used on the web
	  <ol>
	    <li>Glues all the content of the web together</li>
	  </ol>
	<li>Servers - store all the HTML and content  of the web</li>
	<li>Client - personal computers used for viewing web content</li>
	<li>HTTP - protocal used for clients and servers to communicate</li>
	<li>Internet - computer network upon which HTTP requests alr made</li>
      </ol>
    </li>    
    <li>Basics of HTML
      <ol>
	<li>Tags are what HTML uses to tell a browser how to render the content inclosed in them
	  <ol>
	    <li>most tags are meant to have a closing tag but there are a few tags that naturally do not contain content and therefore do not have a closing tag. These are called void tags</ol>
	  </li>
	<li>Elements is the term used to describe a well formed combonation of tags and their coresponding content
	  <ol>
	    <li>elements can be broken down as inline or block
	      <ol>
		<li>block elements create a container around the element whereas inline does not</li>
	      </ol>
	    </li>
	  </ol>
	</li>
	<li>Atributes are modifiers placed inside the opening tag that cam furthur dictate how or what the browser renders</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  </ol>
